    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>World Business Briefing | Europe: Britain: Burberry's Sales Rise</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Burberry Group says third-quarter sales rose by third, bolstered by new stores and brisk sales (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Burberry Group said that third-quarter sales rose by a third, bolstered by new stores and brisk sales of cashmere scarves and coats. Rose Marie Bravo, who has led the charge to revitalize Burberry, is opening stores in large cities like New York. Total retail stores now stand at 129, after seven stores were added in the last three months. Burberry has been one of the few bright spots in a retail industry suffering from economic malaise and a downturn in tourism.</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner (NYT)</p>
      </block>
